'This has been devastating for Dr Korovin,' the source told Radar. 'Her patients are extended family, not just the celebrities. She has been unable to sleep and has been hounded by the media.

'She will absolutely cooperate with investigators from the New York Health Department and Medical Examiner's Office.' 

Rivers, who rose to fame as a guest on The Tonight Show, died aged 81 after she stopped breathing and went into cardiac arrest during the routine surgery.

She was rushed to nearby Mout Sinai hospital, where she was put on life support, but never regained consciousness. She passed away on September 4.

Earlier this week, Dr Korovin, known as 'throat specialist to the stars', released a statement saying she has 'no comment' to make about the tragic incident.

However, sources close to the medic have accused CNN - who originally published the story of her alleged involvement - of 'making up lies'.  

